snippet.textDisplay: Man... this made me sad... like, almost teary. What a tragedy Pokemon has become for us longtime fans. Just like Star Wars, Alien, and Star Trek... I hate to keep seeing once great IPs ruined. Though I had looked forward to this game eagerly when I had initially learned about it, due to the failings of the game and the lies of it's developers, I sat this one out and sadly acknowledge that the next one will likely either overcompensate too far or just continue along this tragic path. I'm glad my last Pokemon was X and Y, that seems to be where the series peaked... and it was where I was able to build my perfect team.

snippet.textDisplay:
One of the only good things to come out of this mess was the sweater youngster. As for the unremarkable "sales record," it's only referring to the console itself, because clearly you're going to break "records" when you're worth $100 billion and your only top-sellers are Mario and Zelda (with all three franchises happening to benefit from some of the most delusional zealots around).

And just like how they've degraded into only caring about making money, this site has degraded from infestuous Squarespace ads randomly appearing in every video. Because there's never enough woeful irony to indulge in.

snippet.textDisplay: Here's my journey with pokemon. After generation 4 I have given up on the franchise,  therefore I did not buy White/Black nor have ever played it. Then my niece was born and she got into pokemon because of me. So I bought X and Y so we can play together. We didn't,  she played it for a short time and never touched it again. It was then that I declared "I'm done with pokemon! Unless they finally make a wolf pokemon." Sun and Moon introduced Lycanroc. Played it, then I said to myself "Why am I playing this game. It's the same shit everytime! I'm done with pokemon!" Next game legendary pokemon is a wolf. "Dammit, one more time, but this is it!"

snippet.textDisplay: I guess I'll recommend pokemon collosseum and pokemon xd gale of darkness for anyone looking for a spin on the formula. You can only catch a limited selection of "shadow pokemon," but it ends up making each pokemon that much more special. All the battles are double battles, making way for actual strategy in the combat. Type-based gym battles are ditched in favor of bosses that use strategies specific to them that need to be overcome. There are some genuinely clever techniques used toward the end. That said, I do have nostalgia goggles, so don't just take my word for it. check out some reviews and see if it's up your alley.

snippet.textDisplay: I honestly enjoyed the game, my gripes are more with the story, Wild Area and lack of creative routes. Like the routes are beautiful at times but not super challenging. The Story felt very secondary to the "Complete the Gym Challenge" A Plot where in past games there was a nice mix of the A and B plot lines whereas here it was like Leons gets to do all the cool stuff cause Ive gotta complete my challenge. The Wild Area while vast and a fresh idea was tackled well. Yeah theres a dip in quality there but most of the time Im not paying attention to the trees or blades of grass. I love pokemon and dont hate this game, but its got its issues, but as an experience I really loved it.

snippet.textDisplay:
Because of subreddits that are just echo chambers of hype-praise and me losing interest in Pokémon around the DS era, I actually thought with every "new" iteration that I just wasn't "getting it". Let's try the demo I says and see what's new. The same child venturing out on a journey with a completely missed opportunity for a coming of age story progression. The same childish dialog. The same turn based battles that haven't changed, implemented rhythm based combat or new strategies.

In 1998 unboxing a Red Pokemon cartridge and playing a game that seemed so large was exciting, I didn't even watch the cartoon, I was in it purely for those pixelated pets - but over 2 decades later the game seems smaller than ever. Just vote with your wallet and know that the game you thought would happen in 2019 can be found elsewhere.

Mystery Dungeon is really cool too, and has a bit more in gameplay from what I've seen! You may really enjoy those if you haven't tried them already.

Thank you for the quality content as always, Shelby and Matt!! 🎉
